In addition, the type of employment exercised has a wide influence on maternity, but less on the date of the beginning of common life," explains CSIC researcher Margarita Delgado.
The level of study is another factor that increases the gap between the age of women and their first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of training is, the more they get married and have their first child late.
The difference is also maintained among women of the same generation.
