In these days of bad times and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are brought back to a garage, where an expert has to assess the damage suffered and the cost of repair.
Each disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and working time can be a long and complex work.
Calculate by hand the cost of repair between €20,000 and €30 000, including parts and the work hand can take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the assistance of the most recent computer tools, this would be a matter of minutes.
For this reason, almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Providers of services and solutions for disaster assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers, then treating them and offering them to their customers as a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American Group Solara, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies in competition in the field of evaluation tools and information processing are GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by the manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
Furthermore, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, so much so that more versions, variants and motorizations have been launched in the last five years than in the previous 15 years.
When a new car leaves the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very hard work, because each of the thousands of pieces of the vehicle must be cataloged and recorded.
In addition, there is a "smart" graphic image of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a car.
If this is a mass-sold model, work can be done within a week if the process progresses very quickly.
If this is a small car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of the cars marketed in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have, for example, information about the Porsche, but not about the Ferraris or Lamborghini.
With regard to vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99 %.
In order to carry out the documentation and development of databases, Audex has eight centres around the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in some brands.
The national seat is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than one hundred technicians (generally mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million each year to develop these databases.
Each month 2.5 million data are recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and offer various products.
The most frequent application concerns repair and maintenance, but according to countries, there are also tools for the management of parts of the case or to calculate the value of a car's vein or residual value.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of opportunity cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but it does it in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, the product being AudaPlus, the standard disaster assessment solution for experts.
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it takes into account the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint barge.
This tool is purchased according to its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is EUR 5.75 for low-use customers at least ten times a month.
Then each insurance company, which carries out thousands of experts, negotiates its price with Audex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it comes out of the mounting chain, only thanks to its chassis number.
